result.execSummary:
The defendant Brandi L Ollins was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Harboring/Aiding a Felon, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.47(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Brandi L Ollins in court with attorney Diane Rose Caspari.  Grant Huebner appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by counsel and defendant.  Additional statements made Katrina K. and Chris O.
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 3.5 YEARS, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 25 days time served.; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 1.5 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 2 YEARS with the following conditions:
*Alcohol and drug assessment and comply with any treatment deemed necessary by the department.
*Mental health assessment and comply with any treatment deemed necessary by the department.
*Absolute sobriety
*No contact with co-defendants: Demetrius Robinson and Davon Thompson.
*No contact with Jordan Wilder's family.
*Random urine screens. 
*Seek and maintain  fulltime employment.
*Pay restitution joint and several in the sum of $4,525.00 to Roxanne W.
*Cognitive Behavior Therapy
*Vocational/educational training
*Pay supervision fees.
The court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 3 years with the following conditions:
*Defendant to serve 12 months in the House of Correction.  No good time credit.  Court stayed sentence to be used as sanctions.  Court ordered defendant to serve 10 days STRAIGHT time for 1st violation; 30 days STRAIGHT time for 2nd violation and balance as STRAIGHT time for 3rd violation.
*Alcohol and drug assessment and comply with any treatment deemed necessary by the department.
*Mental health assessment and comply with any treatment deemed necessary by the department.
*Absolute sobriety
*No contact with co-defendants: Demetrius Robinson and Davon Thompson.
*No contact with Jordan Wilder's family.
*Random urine screens. 
*Seek and maintain  fulltime employment.
*Pay restitution joint and several in the sum of $4,525.00 to Roxanne H..
*Cognitive Behavior Therapy
*Vocational/educational training
*Pay supervision fees.

Court denied defendant's motion for expungement.  

Court ordered defendant to provide DNA sample and imposed mandatory surcharges.
Defendant to pay DNA SURCHARGE and all other costs and any other surcharges during probation and/or by the Department of Corrections from 25% of prison funds and to convert to civil judgment upon release to/from extended supervision or successful completion of probation.
Restitution is to be collected during probation or collected by the DOC from 25% of prison funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b), Wis. Stats. an during extended supervision.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
Bail to be applied.

Probation may be served outside of the state of Wisconsin if accepted.

Court informed defendant she is not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program or Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon she may not possess any firearms.
Court advised defendant that she may not vote until civil rights are restored.
